    <td align="left" valign="middle" class="newsSubject"><img src="/images/clear.gif" width="9" height="10">EQ Forums Closes its Doors</td><td class="newsSubject"><div align="right"><a class="comment" href="#top"><img src="/images/news/top.gif" border="0" alt="Return to Top"></a><img src="/images/clear.gif" width="9" height="10"><a class="comment" href="mailto:eqnews@stratics.com?subject=News"><img src="/images/news/submitnews.gif" border="0" alt="Submit News!"></a><img src="/images/clear.gif" width="9" height="10"><a class="comment" href=""><img src="/images/news/forums.gif" border="0" alt="Comment on this article"></a><img src="/images/clear.gif" width="9" height="10"></div></td>
        </tr>
      </table>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="3" valign="top">   
<tr><td align="left" class="newsCategory">CommunityNews - <font align="left" class="newsDate">11:36 AM PST</font></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top" class="newsText">Here's the announcement from the administrator, Berek Halfhand:<blockquote>As many of you know I have been developing <a href="http://www.eq-forums.com" target="_blank">EQ Forums</a>, a website where the EQ and EQII communities could gather together and discuss both EverQuest games. It has become clear to me that this is not as feasible as I had hoped. Not only is there a line seperating the communities, but also the simple fact that there are plenty of other sites out there for both communities. There is simply no need for a one stop place. Here is what I had to say at EQ Forums - <blockquote><p>It is my sad duty to inform you that EQ Forums is closing its doors for the time being, most likely permanently. <p>It has been a fun adventure developing the website and attempting to bring in a common EQ community. With so many other sites out there for both communities, there is simply no room for the likes of EQ Forums. Developing the site and maintaining it alone has been one of the major problems. As many of you know I work for EQII Stratics and will be devoting more of my time there. You can expect some great changes in EQII Stratics in the near future. <p>Where is the short story series going? If anyone has had a chance to read and enjoy the short stories I write, I will be moving them over to EQII Stratics in a new yet to be named feature. <p>I want to thank everyone here who has helped in trying to get the website up and running by posting blurbs and other information. I hope to see you at EQII Stratics and EQ Stratics as well as the many other sites out there. <p>Cheers, <p>Berek Halfhand</blockquote></blockquote>Sad to see it go, but good to see his Talent will still be put to good use.  :)</td></tr>
