<tr><td align="left" class="newsCategory">CommunityNews - <font align="left" class="newsDate">10:11 AM PST</font></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top" class="newsText">Here's the announcement:<br><br><blockquote>There's a debate that goes on every day at GameSpy.com: which game was better? DOOM or Half-Life? Final Fantasy or Zelda? Warcraft or StarCraft? Robotron or Joust? EverQuest or Ultima Online?<br><br>Over the course of six weeks throughout February, March and April, GameSpy running Title Fight! The Ultimate Gaming Grudge, where you get to cast your votes for what you think are the greatest games of all time. The rules are simple: starting with a bracket of 64 games, they're running different head-to-head matchups every day. You keep voting for your favorites, and in the beginning of April, they'll crown their overall champion. <br><br>Todays Titlefight on Gamespy is going to be EQ vs. UO!  EQ players can log onto Gamespy and vote for the game. Voting begins at Noon today (Monday, February 23, 2004) and runs through Noon tomorrow.</blockquote>Enjoy!<br></td></tr>
<tr><td valign="top" class="newsText"><div align="center">[ <a href="http://boards.stratics.com/php-bin/eq/showflat.php?Cat=&Board=eqwestwood&Number=803004&page=0&view=&sb=5">Comment on this article</a> ]</div></td></tr>


